FBIS3-30746 "dreeu026_k_94007" FBIS-EEU-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 CROATIA Personnel Changes in Internal Affairs Ministry LD0702193594 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 7 Feb 94 LD0702193594 Zagreb HTV Television Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] This evening, President Franjo Tudjman received Internal Affairs Minister Ivan Jarnjak, together with his aides. Following the meeting a statement was issued outlining personnel changes in the Internal Affairs Ministry of the Republic of Croatia. Under a presidential decree, Zlatko Gledec was appointed deputy internal affairs minister; Mladen Lackovic was appointed assistant internal affairs minister responsible for information and personnel; Zellko Tomljenovic, the outgoing deputy minister of internal affairs of the Republic of Croatia, was appointed ministerial adviser.
